docs {
  ## Submit Proposer Slashing

  Submit a signed proposer slashing to the beacon node to be broadcast to the network.

  ### Request Body
  A proposer slashing object containing:
  - `signed_header_1`: First signed beacon block header (message with slot, proposer_index, parent_root, state_root, body_root + signature)
  - `signed_header_2`: Second signed beacon block header (conflicting with the first)

  ### Response (200)
  Proposer slashing is stored in the pool and broadcast to the network. Returns 200 on success.
}
